Prince Harry, the Duke of Sussex, says he and Duchess Meghan &quot;genuinely couldn&#39;t think of a better place to announce the upcoming baby, be it a boy or a girl,&quot; on the first day of the couple&#39;s 16-day tour of Australia, Fiji, Tonga and New Zealand. https://t.co/m1CblP5KDT pic.twitter.com/4FhIgVmufn — Good Morning America (@GMA) October 16, 2018

And today, during his Invictus Games Opening Ceremony speech, Harry couldn&#39;t help but share the happy news again. &quot;First of all, thank you for the welcome you have given Meghan and I over the last few days,&quot; he told participants, staff and volunteers in Sydney per Hello!. &quot;I have been so proud to be able to introduce my wife to you and we have been so happy to be able to celebrate the personal joy of our newest addition with you all.&quot;

The royal addressed the crowd before artists and dancers performed at the Sydney Opera House. Leading up to his speech, Harry practiced in front of Meghan.

